    <div xml:id="PN340">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>aṇittaḻai nuṭaṅka vōṭi maṇippoṟik</l>
<l>kuralaṅ kuṉṟi koḷḷu miḷaiyōḷ</l>
<l>māmakaḷ<gap quantity="48" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="26" reason="lost" unit="character"/>leṉa viṉavuti kēṇī</l>
<l>veṭuppave<gap quantity="34" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="29" reason="lost" unit="character"/>maintar tantai</l>
<l>yirumpaṉai yaṉṉa peruṅkai yāṉai</l>
<l>karantaiyañ ceṟuviṟ peyarkkum</l>
<l>peruntakai maṉṉarkku varaintirun taṉaṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>“The young one who runs so that [her] decorative leaf [skirt] sways</l>
<l>[and] who takes Kuṉṟi seeds from the ears with jewel dots,</l>
<l>the dark girl………………………</l>
<l>………………….” you will ask. Listen:</l>
<l>……………………………..</l>
<l>[Her] father of warriors</l>
<l>sits, having limited [his] choice] to paragon kings,</l>
<l>who bring back from the Karantai fight</l>
<l>elephants with trunks large like big palmyra trees.  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
